SCP 6513: "All-Knowing Ape"

Object Class: Euclid

Special Containment Procedures: SCP-6513 is to be contained in a standard 1 acre wildlife bio-dome with a simulated environment of North Africa. The dome is to be kept at an average temperature of 30 Celsius, with an average humidity of 40-50% percent. Furnishing is allowed within the environment following staff approval. Clothing requests are to be ignored. SCP-6513 is to be fed two standard omnivore meals a day, totaling 2500 calories. Snacks may be requested but daily allotment must remain within 1000 calories.SCP-6513 is allowed Class 4(Restricted Visitation) Socialization privileges. Site staff may visit SCP-6513 when not working, although staff performing tasks that require constant focus to avoid contact due to the anomalous nature of 6513. Visitation may be revoked is 6513 misbehaves.

SCP-6513 is not allowed to access anything deemed a writing utensil, or could be used to write unless accompanied by two Level 4 Personnel and accompanying security.

Descrption: SCP-6513, or "Anonymous"(a perfect translation is impossible) is a sapient pongidae mammal of extra-dimensional origin. 6513 is approximately two meters tall with a weight of 100 kilograms. 6513 lacks fur over most of its body, possessing it primarily upon its appendages, pubic area, between the mammary ridges and its head. Unlike other members of pongidae, 6513 is poorly adapted for climbing and is instead better suited for being on the ground. Its bodily chemistry is carbon-based similar to terrestrial life, although saturated with an unknown anomalous energy detectable by thaumatography. Genetic sequencing has revealed that 6513 is related to currently extant mammals, diverging somewhere around the late Cretaceous. 6513 speaks rough Saurian, having taught itself after being provided materials to do so. 6513 also speaks a native language that is only roughly translated.
